provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py, Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py, Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: concurrent.futures.Future — __doc__.__len__()==53; __doc__=='Represents the result of an asynchronous computation.'; __name__=='Future' (len=6); __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24). concurrent.futures.Executor — __doc__.__len__()==67; __doc__=='This is an abstract base class for concrete asynchronous executors.'; __name__=='Executor' (len=8); __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24). concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor — __name__=='ThreadPoolExecutor' (len=18); __module__=='concurrent.futures.thread' (len=25). concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor — __name__=='ProcessPoolExecutor' (len=19); __module__=='concurrent.futures.process' (len=26). concurrent.futures.CancelledError — __doc__.__len__()==25; __doc__=='The Future was cancelled.'; __name__=='CancelledError' (len=14); __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24). concurrent.futures.InvalidStateError — __doc__.__len__()==43; __name__=='InvalidStateError' (len=17); __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24). concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor — __doc__.__len__()==74; __name__=='BrokenExecutor' (len=14); __bases__[0].__name__=='RuntimeError' (len=12). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24: 'concurrent'=10+'.'=1+'futures'=7+'.'=1+'_base'=5=24); same _base module for Executor, CancelledError, InvalidStateError, BrokenExecutor. ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures.thread' (len=25); ProcessPoolExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures.process' (len=26, one more than thread). CancelledError.__bases__[0].__name__=='Error' (len=5): inherits from a base Error class. BrokenExecutor.__bases__[0].__name__=='RuntimeError' (len=12): inherits directly from RuntimeError. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

